Description: Raw meat dripping with blood from a monster.
Name: Meat

Description: An old document that describes how one can turn into a demon. Read what's inside.
Name: Demonic Research: Transformation

Description: A material needed to make a Demon Transform Scroll. A lot of it is needed.
Name: Naktis' Servant's Cloth Scrap

Description: A scroll that allows the user to transform into a demon at any time. The type of demon depends on the materials used to make it, however.
Name: Demon Transform Scroll

Description: A key retrieved from a servant of Naktis.
Name: Old Key

Description: Meat from a monster that can be dedicated to a sanctum. Because it's a lean part of the meat, it doesn't smell that much.
Name: Sacrificial Lean Monster Meat

Description: A crest that can find monsters that have eaten the sanctum's insignia.{nl}It's a symbol of the Cleric Master's faith.
Name: Cleric Master's Symbol of Faith

Description: The tough leather of a monster. Its toughness makes it watertight.
Name: Tough Leather

Description: A pouch made from a monster's Tough Leather
Name: Tough Leather Pouch

Description: A monster's Tough Leather Pouch that has been filled with water.
Name: Water-Filled Leather Pouch

Description: An old and rusted key.
Name: Old Key

Description: The sixth revelation found in the Great Cathedral. Readable.
Name: Revelation of Great Cathedral

Description: - How to Use{nl}During the Pitch-pot game, use the 'Pitch-pot Coin' item to charge the gauge, and use the normal attack button to stop the charge. This will adjust the strength to throw the coin.{nl}If the coin lands inside the pot, it will measure how far it was thrown and the precision to calculate points gained.{nl}Upon moving maps, your points and the 'Pitch-pot Coin' will be deleted.
Name: Pitch-pot Coin

Description: Soccer Ball
Name: Soccer Ball

Description: Installs a barricade which deters opposing guild members for 600 seconds.{nl}Can be used only by members of the guild defending the Spot.{nl}Provides the following bonus when the user is a Squire, Alchemist or Pardoner:{nl}    - Barricade durability +20%
Name: [GTW] Wooden Barricade

Description: Installs a weapon that shoots arrows in a single shot or in continuous shots at members of rival guilds within range for 600 seconds. The arrows include knockback and stunning effects.{nl}Can be used only by members of the guild defending the Spot.{nl}Provides the following bonus when the user is a Squire, Alchemist or Pardoner:{nl}    - Ballista durability and attack +20%
Name: [GTW] Ballista

Description: Installs a mobile tower that attacks members or installations of opposing guilds for 600 seconds. Ride the tower in order to direct it and attack. Fits up to 5 players.{nl}Can be used only by members of the guild defending the Spot.{nl}Provides the following bonus when the user is a Squire, Alchemist or Pardoner:{nl}    - Tower durability and attack +20%
Name: [GTW] Siege Tower

Description: Installs a flag that allows you to move to the spot where it is planted for 180 seconds when using a [GTW] Warp Scroll - GTW.{nl}Can be used only by members of the guild defending the Spot.{nl}Cooldown is shared among all guild members.
Name: [GTW] Divine Flag

Description: Use the Mysterious Crystal when you become incapable of combat to regenerate on the same spot.{nl}Can be used only inside Spot Area maps.
Name: [GTW] Mysterious Crystal

Description: Use to regenerate all fellow guild members currently incapable of combat within the range of your screen, and restore 50% of their HP and SP.{nl}Can be used only inside Spot Area maps.{nl}Cooldown is shared among all guild members.
Name: [GTW] Wide Regeneration Scroll

Description: Use to move to a Spot Area.{nl}You will be directed to the location of the Divine Flag.{nl}Cannot be used inside Spot Areas.{nl}Can only be used by guilds that are not currently seizing the Spot Area.{nl}
Name: [GTW] Warp Scroll - GTW

Description: Use the Mysterious Crystal when you become incapable of combat to regenerate on the same spot.{nl}Can be used only inside Spot Area maps.{nl}Will be automatically deleted at the end of the event period.
Name: [GTW Event] Mysterious Crystal

Description: Use to move to a Spot Area.{nl}You will be directed to the location of the Divine Flag.{nl}Cannot be used inside Spot Areas.{nl}Can only be used by guilds that are not currently seizing the Spot Area.{nl}Will be automatically deleted at the end of the event period.
Name: [GTW Event] Warp Scroll - GTW

Description: Use to reveal for 5 seconds where the members of the defending guild are on the Spot Area.{nl}Can only be used by members of the guilds attacking the Spot.
Name: [GTW] Recon Map

Description: Removes all removable debuffs and applies the following effects when used.{nl}    - Immunity to Knockback/Knockdown for 5 seconds{nl}    - Immunity to all removable debuffs for 5 seconds{nl}    - Boosts movement speed momentarily. Movement speed returns to normal gradually over 5 seconds{nl}Can only be used in Spot Areas.
Name: [GTW] Status Ailment Resistance Potion

Name: mone

Description: Found in the Outer Wall District 15 area. It does not seem to have been used much seeing how it is relatively clean.

Description: Found in the Outer Wall District 15 area. It seems to have seen some use over the years.

Description: A medal confirming your contribution in the battle against Boruta.{nl}Can be exchanged for items by 'Royal Supply Officer Manfredas' at your Guild Hangout.

Description: A soil sample collected from around the Abandoned Workshop. It is severely polluted.

Description: A stolen bag of grain that the soldiers at Shaton Farm took as a bribe.

Description: An antidote that can heal the poisoned farmers.{nl}Get it to them as soon as possible.

Description: A horn that proves that the owner has killed the Tree Root Mole.

Description: A sweet-smelling secretion from a Woodluwa. It can soften hardened honeycombs.

Description: A large cap from the head of a liverwort plant. It exudes a strange smell.

Description: A fragment that broke off a Stonecon. It twitches ever so slightly.

Name: Old Book

Description: A letter found in an old book left behind by a dead man. It contains an order for an assassination as well as a confirmation of its execution.
Name: Seal Stamped Letter

Description: An aquatic plant that grows in watery environments. It can filter and purify water.
Name: Acylado Hydrophyte

Description: A crystal ball found in a wooden box at the monastery. Used to activate the device in the prayer hall.
Name: Monastery Crystal Ball

Description: A strong potion used for removing odors. It has an antiseptic scent to it.
Name: Deodorizing Potion

Description: Scriptures that were scattered by rampaging monsters. Bring them to Mohaim.
Name: Tyla Monastery Scriptures

Description: The objective to activate the shrine is written on one of the magical circle shrines.
Name: Assistant Commander Gomen's Given Memo

Description: The fur of a Green Lepusbunny Assassin. It looks similar to that of an ordinary Lepusbunny, but it seems to have better heat retention.
Name: Lepusbunny Assassin Fur

Description: It seems one might be able to easily find stones to use as flints in the plateau's black boulders.
Name: Flint

Description: A message from the Mesafasla army to the Stogas squad.
Name: Message from Mesafasla

Description: Emergency food carried by the Siaulav Mages for their kind, known for its preparedness.
Name: Siaulav Mage's Emergency Food

Description: These are the main food of the people living in the plateau region.
Name: Plateau Potatoes

Description: It looks like it can be used as a caltrop if you polish it well.
Name: Usable Bar Fragment

Description: Unlike its appearance, it is effective in reducing fever.
Name: Blue Lapasape Spotted Mushroom

Description: Although it doesn't look sharp, it is still a decent handknife to peel off barks from trees.
Name: Horace's Handknife

Description: When there is no food, you should at least consume this to survive.
Name: Plateau Tree's Inner Barks

Description: Looks suitable for crafting a shield.
Name: Dry Wood

Description: Tusks are a Pokuborn's main weapon. They look like they could be used to make shields.
Name: Pokuborn Tusk

Description: A mysterious gem said to be endowed by the Goddess Gabija. They say that this gem can hold the life force of monsters.
Name: Torch Gem

Description: A gem abounding with energy. An adept one could spark a holy fire using this.
Name: Repleted Torch Gem

Description: Holy water used for blessings for those who wishes to take the path of a priest. It seems like it requires the blessings from other clerics.
Name: Holy Water for Blessings

Description: A magical item used to count the number of enemies defeated in combat. Peltasta use it to pass their advancement test.
Name: Combat Enemy Counter

Description: A special medicine from Orsha obtained by Tamara. Although it does not cure completely, its temporary healing power is exceptional.
Name: Special Medicine from Orsha

Description: Items to be offered to the Goddess Statue.
Name: Goods for Offering

Description: Just plain wormwood. Its bitter taste will give you a hard time if you try to eat it.
Name: Wormwood

Description: Like its name suggests, it works as a great remedy to stop hemorrhages.
Name: Hemostasis Herb

Description: A flower that blooms only at night. It offers anti-inflammatory effects.
Name: Moonlight Flower

Description: A chunk of metal consolidated inside a monster.
Name: Ore Crystal

Description: A chisel for stonecrafting made by the blacksmith in Orsha for the Submaster.
Name: Special Order Chisel

Description: A spearhead found in the body of the monster that ran away from Hoplite Master's attack.
Name: Aidas' Lost Spear Tip

Description: A mysterious crystal given by the Krivis Submaster with a request to purify monsters.
Name: Glowing Crystal

Description: The ash remains from a monster purified by the holy fire.
Name: Purified Monster's Ash

Description: The horn of a Sparnasman. Wanted by Zenoa.
Name: Sparnasman's Horn

Description: The energy of the Sadhu Master is crystallized here.
Name: Sadhu's Energy

Description: Traces left by Hoplites using monsters for training.
Name: Hoplites' Broken Spear Parts

Description: Damanged Hoplite armor parts left behind after a fierce battle.
Name: Hoplites' Broken Off Armor Pieces

Description: A type of drug said to be drunk by Barbarians during their training period. Those who drink it deliberately will have their strength reduced. The effects of the drug can be canceled at will.
Name: Barbarian's Medicinal Liquid

Description: Papayams are known to have a distinctively greasy pulp.
Name: Papayam Greasy Pulp

Description: A holy relic cursed with an energy that attracts demons. How many more relics will be cursed?
Name: Old Sacred Object

Description: A compass able to read spells. It can be used to find objects containing protection spells.
Name: Spell Detector Compass

Description: An orb given by Mihail. It can be used to store the magic of defeated monsters.
Name: Empty Magic Orb

Description: An orb filled with magic. Mihail intends to use it to blow up the magic supply device.
Name: Fully-charged Magic Orb

Description: An amulet prepared by Melchioras.{nl}It is said to lift protection spells.
Name: Cast Releasing Amulet

Description: A pouch filled with Magic Concentration Orbs
Name: Magic Orb Pouch

Description: Page 1 of a diary from someone named Ardel, a former resident of the Delmore Castle.
Name: Ardel's Diary, Page 1

Description: Page 2 of a diary from someone named Ardel, a former resident of the Delmore Castle.
Name: Ardel's Diary, Page 2

Description: Page 3 of a diary from someone named Ardel, a former resident of the Delmore Castle.
Name: Ardel's Diary, Page 3

Description: An arrow that once pierced a Charcoal Walker.{nl}It looks like it can still be used.
Name: Useful Arrow

Description: A crystal that finds objects hidden behind magic. Use it to find the magic supply device.
Name: Spell Detector Crystal

Description: A wooden board able to be used as a barricade. Taken from an old wooden crate.
Name: Useful Wooden Board

Description: A mushroom able to boost Melchioras' power.{nl}It doesn't look very tasty.
Name: Thorn Mushroom

Description: Sap that oozes out of a Charog's body. It smells awfully foul.
Name: Charog Sap

Description: A means to affect the souls of monsters.
Name: Yane's Shaman Doll

Description: A crystal for collecting sinister magic. Attach it to the device to destroy it.
Name: Ominous Magic Crystal

Description: An amplifier carried by Black Maizes. An item wanted by Revelator Mihail.
Name: Magic Amplifier

Description: Material needed to create a Bokor doll.
Name: Raffly Soul Crystal

Description: Material needed to create a Bokor doll.
Name: Vubbe Warrior Mind Crystal

Description: Tinis with shining horns are a rare site.
Name: Tini's Shining Horn

Description: Used often by nearby villagers and pilgrims for emergency purposes.
Name: Taumas Herb

Description: Looking at the state that it's in, it seems like the Tini liked it a lot.
Name: Jacob's Lost Luggage

Description: This looks strong enough to sustain the weight of an elderly person.
Name: Sturdy Branch

Description: Considered to taste better than it looks.
Name: Tini Meat

Description: It seems to be in good shape despite being abandoned for a long time.
Name: Firewood

Description: Spion Fur that still has it's fur intact seems to be adept for keeping body heat.
Name: Spion Fur

Description: Fruit discovered in the Brambles of Salvia Forest. It will take a large amount of these to fill a person's stomach.
Name: Salvia Bramble Fruit

Description: Medicine created by Brutus from the Order of the Tree of Truth. Nobody knows what it is created from.
Name: Order's Secret Medicine

Description: Said to burn in a particular bright light.
Name: Flammable Leaves

Description: A rosary crafted at the Maven Abbey. Its main characteristic is that it shines.
Name: Maven Abbey Rosary

Description: The water will react to the demons if this is actually holy water as Monk Dorma suggested.
Name: Monk Dorma's Holy Water

Description: Abandoned roots of a plant. It seems as if they were not fit for human consumption.
Name: Abandoned Plant Roots

Description: The meat of a Lepusbunny is a treat for people that know how good it is.
Name: Lepusbunny Meat

Description: A mirror said to show the true identity of those that are reflected upon it.
Name: Mirror of Truth

Description: The mirror seems to have replenished its energy.
Name: Replenished Mirror of Truth

Description: The rosary of Monk Stella. It does not seem to have any distinguishing features from other Maven Abbey rosaries.
Name: Monk Stella's Rosary

Description: A holy water flask that does not have any contents.
Name: Empty Holy Water Flask

Description: A holy water flask that contains Ouaas Tree Sap. Monk Stella believes it will have the same effects as holy water.
Name: Ouaas Tree Sap

Description: It seems to be far from holy for some reason.
Name: Magic Scroll of Holy Power Enhancement

Description: Fragment from the Suppression Device. It still seems to have some power left in it.
Name: Suppression Device Fragment

Description: It seems as if you will be able to store divine power like any other orb.
Name: Maven Abbey Orb

Description: It seems as if the food is preserved in pristine condition.
Name: Well-preserved Food

Description: Herbs that have not totally dried and crumbled.
Name: Herb of Restoration

Description: Debris from the wall showing that there was some sort of incident here long ago.
Name: Debris from the Wall

Description: It is said to contain documents that will prove Ruklys' innocence.
Name: Ruklys' Document Chest

Description: It is said to contain documents that will prove Ruklys' innocence.
Name: Ruklys' Document Chest

Description: Magic shards that have gathered inside the body of a Blue Gosaru. May be used to recharge the Document Chest's energy.
Name: Blue Gosaru Magic Stone Shards

Description: The key to Ruklys' document chest.
Name: Document Chest's Key

Description: A strong acidic solvent. It appears to be strong enough to dissolve any monster eggs.
Name: Strong Solvent

Description: Spores that are unique to the Yega Bracken that live in Khamadon Forest.
Name: Yega Bracken Spores

Description: Said to put weakened monsters to sleep without fail.
Name: Sleep Powder

Description: Greg has refined the spores you gathered for him, creating a medicine.
Name: Refined Spores

Description: Smells spicy enough now, but will become even worse when burned.
Name: Astrus Herbs

Description: Sophia wishes to research the Centaurus Crystal in order to find out why the Ducky cannot seem to stand their ground against the Centaurus.
Name: Centaurus Crystal

Description: Powder created by crushing Centaurus Crystals
Name: Centaurus Dust

Description: It is said that a lot of Blue Beetow Wings are needed in order to substitute Centaurus poison.
Name: Blue Beetow Wings

Description: Dry bracken leaves that have fallen off of the stem. It can be mixed with Blue Beetow Wings to substitute Centaurus poison.
Name: Dry Bracken Leaves

Description: Can relieve pain for a limited time.
Name: Whitetailed Grass

Description: This must be sprayed on Kugheri Tots in order to obtain a special type of ingredient.
Name: Kugheri Stimulant

Description: Poison sacks discovered on stimulated Kugheri Tots. You can almost see the strong poison.
Name: Stimulated Poison Sacks

Description: Strange smelling Kugheri Paralysis Poison. Used to paralyze small animals.
Name: Kugheri Paralysis Poison

Description: A special trap crafted by Vilhelmas, designed with the plan in mind.
Name: Vilhelmas' Trap

Description: It tastes terrible but is still edible for anyone desperate enough to eat it.
Name: Leafnut Tailfruit

Description: It may turn out to be a usable weapon if properly trimmed.
Name: Sturdy Stick

Description: The juices from a Pystis Grass Root are used in a variety of medicine.
Name: Pystis Grass Roots

Description: It is said that it can cure the plague when mixed with Pystis Grass Root juice.
Name: Orange Grummer Legs

Description: It is said that Red Colimen Fluid is effective at disolving moss.
Name: Red Colimen Fluid

Description: A chest holding memories of Lord Ryudhas.
Name: Small Jeweled Chest

Description: A shield that has the seal of the Joquvas family on it.
Name: Joquvas Family Shield

Description: It is said that a lot of dew gathers on Syla Dandelions.
Name: Syla Dandelion Dew

Description: Part of the orders given to the Kugheri Tribe by the demon named Vhalteras.
Name: Demon Orders

Description: A chest that has been secretly passed down the Royal Family. It is said to contain clues on finding Taniel the Second's Royal Mausoleum.
Name: Royal Family Chest

Description: A map containing the locations of magical trees related to the Secret Royal Mausoleum. Can be unfolded.
Name: Map to the Magical Trees

Description: A magical slate that has also been passed down the Royal Family, bearing the seal of the Royal Family. It is said to react to magical trees and is somehow related to the Secret Royal Mausoleum.
Name: Seal of the Royal Family

Description: The seal has lost its glow as it has used all of its power.
Name: Dull Royal Family Seal

Description: The seal has lost its glow as it has used all of its power.
Name: Dull Royal Family Seal

Description: The seal has lost its glow as it has used all of its power.
Name: Dull Royal Family Seal

Description: The seal has lost its glow as it has used all of its power.
Name: Dull Royal Family Seal

Description: The seal has lost its glow as it has used all of its power.
Name: Dull Royal Family Seal

Description: A note with memos from Indraja written on it. Readable.
Name: Indraja's note

Description: A ceremonial staff that the Kugheri Numani carry around. The bells on it appear to have some sort of shamanic powers.
Name: Kugheri Shaman Staff

Description: An ancient book that had been stored in the Royal Library. It is made of parchment.
Name: Ancient Parchment Book

Description: A handknife that you have received from Ella. You may be able to retrieve juice from the exposed tree roots.
Name: Ella's Handknife

Description: Juice retrieved from the contaminated tree roots in the destroyed city.
Name: Tree Root Juice

Description: Fake parchment created by Ella in order to fool the goblins.
Name: Fake Parchment

Description: Books that are in acceptable condition despite being damaged.
Name: Acceptable Book

Description: A pouch holding keepsakes from the advance party. The goblins seem to carry them around as loot.
Name: Advance Party's Keepsakes

Description: A pendulum used by Royal Investigators as a special sign. Gasper believes that it will lead them to relics hidden by the advance party.
Name: Investigation Team's Pendulum

Description: Records found by the advance party. It looks as if they were able to hide it before being ambushed by goblins.
Name: Hidden Slate

Description: Sturdy vines that have gone through the building's roof.
Name: Usable Vines

Description: It glows in dark places as it contains the magic from Goblin Shamans.
Name: Goblin Shaman's Jewel

Description: Required to complete the Event Daily Quests.
Name: Monster Badge

Description: An orb that was given to you from the Beholder. You can use the orb to absorb magical sources of energy.
Name: Beholder's Orb

Description: An orb that was given to you from the Beholder, now filled with magical energy. There is so much magic stored that the orb's original color has become turbid.
Name: Magic Infused Orb

Description: A shining tool that was dropped by a Carapace. In the center of the tool, there are beads that shimmer with a bright blue light.
Name: Light Blue Wing

Description: A magical tool that negates the magical effects from the Beholder. Kill nearby monsters and demons and use their souls to fuel the Dispel Tool.
Name: Empty Dispel Magic Tool

Description: A magic tool that negates the magical effects from the Beholder. The tool is currently packed full of souls and energy.
Name: Magic Infused Dispel Tool

Description: Matches obtained from the Resistance Group. It has various uses.
Name: Resistance Supplies Match

Description: Reciprocal parchment prepared by the Resistance Army Recruiter to prepare a report on the junction.
Name: Records Parchment

Description: Report of Zibukas Crossroad. Its written with plants and water of lake monsters and demons and other anomalies
Name: Zibukas Crossroas Report

Description: A low-grade oil bottle carried by resistance scouts. It is primarily used for sending signals
Name: Scout's Oil Bottle

Description: Leaves obtained from monsters growing in the lake. The leaves are very moist as if they had just been watered.
Name: Lakeland Leaves

Description: An unprocessed bomb given to you from Solcomm. When combined with the right components it can become a powerful bomb that is capable of nullifying magic
Name: Unprocessed Bomb

Description: A very powerful bomb. It is said that it can even penetrate through objects embedded in protective magic.
Name: Magic Nullification Bomb

Description: The roots you can get from Lily Velly and Jily Velly. The mysterious aura drifts somewhere because it grows up in the water of the lake.
Name: Moist Roots

Description: A magical powder found in the Demon's Warehouse. The powder's magical substance is capable of enhancing the strength of other materials.
Name: Magical Catalyst Powder

Description: A supply bottle that was distributed to the resistance troops as supplies. The bottle is quite heavy as it has been filled up by Leonildas.
Name: Resistance Supplies Bottle

Description: Fluid that was created using the spirit of the lake. It was created using the leaves of the monsters that drank the lake's water and a catalyst to increase the effectiveness.
Name: Spiritually Infused Lakeland Sap

Description: An arrow found stuck in a demon. Do you think the owner of this arrow is a newcomer who left to find his deputy?
Name: Used Arrow

Description: A piece of cloth that the demon had. The color of the cloth looks quite similar to the cloth used on Schaffenstar uniforms.
Name: Blue-colored Cloth

Description: A pendant found on the demon. Upon opening the pendant the face of a man can be seen inside of it. Is he the owner of this pendant?
Name: Someone's Pendant

Description: A dagger that was stuck in the back of a Tutu. Upon closer inspection you can see the letters'Leonardas'engraved on the handle.
Name: Dirk Inside Tutu's Body

Description: Crops grown at the Gytis Settlement Area. Unfortunately they all withered and died.
Name: Dead Crops

Description: Goods lost by a merchant. Includes all sorts of objects intended for sale.
Name: Lost Goods

Description: Goods lost by a merchant. Includes pricier objects intended for sale.
Name: Expensive Goods

Description: A ledger, apparently belonging to a merchant. Contains all sorts of transaction records.
Name: Merchant Ledger

Description: Holy water distributed by a Priest. Can be used to purify the contaminated landmarks of Starving Demon's Way.
Name: Priest-grade Holy Water

Description: A shadow trace acquired from an Incarnated Shadow at Ziburynas Forest
Name: Shadow Trace of Ziburynas Forest

Description: A shadow trace acquired from an Incarnated Shadow at Khonot Forest
Name: Shadow Trace of Khonot Forest

Description: A shadow trace acquired from an Incarnated Shadow at Lhadar Forest
Name: Shadow Trace of Lhadar Forest

Description: A shadow trace acquired from an Incarnated Shadow at Namu Temple Ruins
Name: Shadow Trace of Namu Temple Ruins

Description: A Research Device created by the Shadowmancer Master for her research. To prevent further exposure from the device, it's being placed in a container to prevent it from leaking.
Name: Shadowmancer Master's Research Device

Description: A token made by Anastazija as proof of all the locations she explored. 'I, Anastazija, have explored this entire region'Is engraved on the back of the token.
Name: Adventurer's Token

Description: This is a pouch given to you by the Sapper Master. As you walk you can hear a soft jingling sound coming from it.
Name: A pouch given by the Sapper Master.

Description: This is a key given to you by the Linker Submaster. It's made from the materials you gathered. With this key, you will be able to entered the Two dimensional world found in Tenet Church 1F.
Name: A Key from the Linker Submaster

Description: Quest Reward. Gives 100 Attribute Points. Right-click to use.
Name: Attribute Points: 100

Description: A device used to suppress the magic of portals.
Name: Portal Suppressor

Description: A bomb for destroying portals. Use it to eliminate the portals created by the demons.
Name: Portal Bomb

Description: A magic stone fragment that was being held by a demon. Kron wants to use it to create a bomb that can destroy the magic protecting the defensive devices.
Name: Magic Stone Fragment

Description: A bomb made from magic stone fragments. It may be slow to detonate, but the explosion it produces is powerful enough.
Name: Magic Stone Bomb

Description: This lever can be connected to the first defensive device in order to deactivate the trap.
Name: First Device Lever

Description: A document obtained from nearby demons containing instructions from a superior. They describe what to do on 4F.
Name: Written Instructions

Description: This lever can be connected to the second defensive device in order to deactivate the trap.
Name: Second Device Lever

Description: A key belonging to Elder Henika. It exudes an unpleasant energy. You will need it to use the elevator to 21F.
Name: Elder Henika's Key

Description: Emergency medicine commonly provided to members of the Schaffenstar. It includes a powerful antidote. Somehow it was in the hands of a demon.
Name: Schaffenstar Emergency Meds

Description: A handle that controls the barrier that's hiding the first defensive device on 12F. You can connect it to the control device and turn the handle to disable it.
Name: Control Device Handle

Description: This lever can be connected to the first defensive device in order to deactivate the trap.
Name: First Device Lever

Description: This lever can be connected to the second defensive device in order to deactivate the trap.
Name: Second Device Lever

Description: A key belonging to Elder Adaux. It exudes an unpleasant energy. You will need it to use the elevator to 21F.
Name: Elder Adaux's Key

Description: A scroll being kept by the Schaffenstar members guarding the control device. You can use it to find magic sources hidden nearby.
Name: Suspicious Scroll

Description: This lever can be connected to the defensive device in order to deactivate the trap.
Name: Defensive Device Lever

Description: A key to the General Office on 20F, taken from the demons. It can be used to find another key.
Name: First General Office Key

Description: Another key to the General Office on 20F. It can be used with the other office key to operate the elevator to 21F.
Name: Second General Office Key

Description: An arrow given by Byle. It may not be powerful enough to stop Elder Henika, but it can weaken the demons.
Name: Magic Arrow

Description: A key belonging to Elder Cezaris. It exudes an unpleasant energy. You will need it to use the elevator to 21F.
Name: Elder Cezaris' Key

Description: Traces of magic found scattered around. Byle wants to use them to overload the demon devices.
Name: Magic Residue

Description: The tenth Revelation, found at the Astral Tower. Readable.
Name: Astral Tower Revelation

Description: A red bookmark that can be used to decipher the code used in the Fantasy Library. You need to place all the bookmarks in the correct order to open the portal.
Name: Red Bookmark

Description: A yellow bookmark that can be used to decipher the code used in the Fantasy Library. You need to place all the bookmarks in the correct order to open the portal.
Name: Yellow Bookmark

Description: A green bookmark that can be used to decipher the code used in the Fantasy Library. You need to place all the bookmarks in the correct order to open the portal.
Name: Green Bookmark

Description: A blue bookmark that can be used to decipher the code used in the Fantasy Library. You need to place all the bookmarks in the correct order to open the portal.
Name: Blue Bookmark

Description: Story of the Legendary Archer and Arrow Maker. Readable.
Name: Lydia Schaffen and the Fletcher

Description: No target is invisible for a trained archer! Readable.
Name: Lydia Schaffen Crossroads

Description: Advice on the use of tools given by Lydia Schaffen to her apprentices. Readable.
Name: Lydia Schaffen's Notch

Description: The challenges faced by Lydia Schaffen and her solutions. Readable.
Name: Lydia Schaffen and Rumpelstiltskin

Description: Essential Reading for Linkers: Finding The Nexus Point Of All Ego. Not readable.
Name: The Expansion of Atman

Description: A research paper on armors used during the rule of King Kadumel. Not readable.
Name: Armor from the Kadumel Era

Description: A book sought after by the Sage Master. Not readable.
Name: Sage Baseline

Description: A book sought after by the Sage Master. Not readable.
Name: The Goddess' Abode of Mount Monderor Volume I

Description: A book sought after by the Sage Master. Not readable.
Name: Book of the Void

Description: A lamp that collects mana from the air around it.
Name: Mana Lamp

Description: Use to carry a festival balloon.{nl}Will be automatically deleted at the end of the event period.
Name: Balloon: 평

Description: Use to carry a festival balloon.{nl}Will be automatically deleted at the end of the event period.
Name: Balloon: 생

Description: Use to carry a festival balloon.{nl}Will be automatically deleted at the end of the event period.
Name: Balloon: 겜

Description: Use to carry a festival balloon.{nl}Will be automatically deleted at the end of the event period.
Name: Balloon: ♥

Description: An order given out to the demons of Outer Wall District 11. It is indecipherable as it is written in the language of demons.
Name: Demon Orders

Description: A potion given to you by the Druid Master. Use to transform into a demon that you have come across before.
Name: Transformation Potion

Description: A purifier given to you by the Taoist Master. It looks like ordinary yellow paper, but it takes effect when attached to evil objects.
Name: Purifier

Description: A holy water given to you by the Exorcist Master. Spray on weakened demons to purify their souls.
Name: Purifying Holy Water

Description: A small statue given to you by the Exorcist Master. Carry it around to collect ominous energy that is harnessed by the state to produce greater power.
Name: Statue of Purification

Description: A grenade found in the Armory. Throw them to make them go boom.
Name: Grenade

Description: Common explosives found in abundance in the Armory. You can only carry one at a time because of its weight. Be careful with them as they are highly volatile.
Name: Explosives

Description: Crystal pieces dropped by demons around the Obelisk in the Training Grounds. They could be a clue to destroying the Obelisk.
Name: Red Crystal Piece

Description: Crystal pieces dropped by demons around the Obelisk in the Training Grounds. They could be a clue to destroying the Obelisk.
Name: Blue Crystal Piece

Description: Crystal pieces dropped by demons around the Obelisk in the Training Grounds. They could be a clue to destroying the Obelisk.
Name: Yellow Crystal Piece

Description: Crystal pieces dropped by demons around the Obelisk in the Training Grounds. They could be a clue to destroying the Obelisk.
Name: Green Crystal Piece

Description: An item given to you by Antanina. Antanina wants you to use this item on the demon portals in Outer Wall District 13 to inhibit them.
Name: Portal Suppressor

Description: A memo written by the Resistance Adjutant Antanina. It is a to-do list of missions in Outer Wall District 13. Right-click to use.
Name: Antanina's Note

Description: Can be used on Scarecrows to make the Wicked Witch vulnerable to attacks.{nl}Removed when the event dungeon has been exited.
Name: Spoiled Candy

Description: Matches that you have received from Sigis. They are useful for cremating the dead.
Name: Gravekeeper's Match

Description: A doll from the grave keeper that possesses magic.
Name: Grave Keeper's Spell Doll

Description: A soul stone that absorbs the thoughts of the resurrected dead when they were alive.
Name: Evil Thoughts Stone

Description: A stone that has the property to burn easily. You should be careful so that the flame doesn't get on it.
Name: Gintas' Flint

Description: A Spirit Rock filled with spirits. Take it to Margiris to be recognized as a member of the sect.
Name: Full Soul Stone

Description: A list that contains the names of the manor owners at the Kaliss region. You will need a bonfire to burn it.
Name: Manor Owner List

Description: A black crystal that was obtained from the resurrected dead. It's a trace of the evil magic that resurrected the dead.
Name: Evil Magic Trace

Description: A part of the list of the manor owners which Carlyle hid. Currently unreadable.
Name: Hidden List (1)

Description: A part of the list of the manor owners which Carlyle hid. Currently unreadable.
Name: Hidden List (2)

Description: A part of the list of the manor owners which Carlyle hid. Currently unreadable.
Name: Hidden List (3)

Description: A part of the list of the manor owners which Carlyle hid. Currently unreadable.
Name: Hidden List (4)

Description: The herb requested by Leja
Name: Bellai Forest Healing Herb

Description: The stolen food by ferrets.
Name: Stolen Food by Ferrets

Description: A juice extracted by a ferrit from a gigantic fruit.
Name: Gigantic Fruit Juice

Description: Contaminated water taken from an old well. Do NOT drink this unless you like to suffer pain.
Name: Dirty Red Water from the Well

Description: A statue made by Dievdirbys Widas. It pacifies the ferrets nearby.
Name: Widas' Statue

Description: Grass that makes someone drowsy. You should be careful not to lose your consciousness.
Name: Drowsy Herb

Description: A pouch of Drousy Herb made by Druid Leja. It is said to make ferrets in the surrounding area confused when activated. Can be used 3 times.
Name: Bag of Drowsy Herb Incense

Description: The orb that was left by the Goddess Laima. You've received the message from Goddess Laima to rescue Goddess Lada.
Name: Goddess' Orb

Description: A scroll with nothing written on it. Observe the ferrets like Benes requested and write down their behavior patterns on this scroll.
Name: Empty Scroll

Description: A transformation scroll that Benes gave to you. When you use it, you can transform into a ferret.
Name: Ferret Transformation Scroll

Description: A piece of wood that turned into an injured villager by Benes' witchcraft.
Name: Voodooed Wooden Piece

Description: A terrible scent that was given by Druid Benes. When you spread it, the ferrets will run away.
Name: Terrible Scent

Description: The blood of a demon that you have obtained from a demon. When you sprinkle it on the device of absorbing vitalities, the device will break.
Name: Demon Blood

Description: A purification scroll made by the Druid Master. It is said to purify grounds contaminated with evil energy.
Name: Purification Scroll

Description: A seed of the Earth Flower. When you plant it, it will absorb the energy of the earth and the flower will grow.
Name: Earth Flower Seed

Description: A flower of the earth full of vitalities that grew on the land. You can feel its strong vitality.
Name: Earth Flower of Vigor

Description: A red crystal obtained from a demon. With this temperature you could burn anything.
Name: Burning Crystal

Description: A soul that has turned red due to the influence from demons. It seems too late to undo the effects.
Name: Red Cursed Soul

Description: A soul that has turned blue due to the influence from demons. It seems too late to undo the effects.
Name: Blue Cursed Soul

Description: A pendulum used to find hidden objects. It sometimes seems to react when hunting monsters.
Name: Pendulum

Description: A note left by Adomas.'Run away from Faustas''is what it says. Deliver it to a Necromancer named Lemija.
Name: Adomas' Note

Description: A letter from a soldier. It seems to have been written to their family, but it was never delivered.
Name: Old Letter

Description: A piece of a defeated monster's corpse. Lemija says it can be used to make an amulet.
Name: Monster Corpse Piece

Description: An amulet made by Lemija. It can absorb the magic occupying the body of the frozen soldier.
Name: Lemija's Amulet

Description: A note by the Assistant Commander of Vedas Plateau. It describes the situation of the region.
Name: Assistant Commander's Note

Description: Objects obtained from monsters. They seem to be souvenirs for the soldier.
Name: Vedas Plateau Soldier's Belongings

Description: A ring given by the Assistant Commander of Vedas Plateau. Deliver it to Royal Army Officer Retia.
Name: Engagement Ring

Description: A reagent chemical found in an abandoned tent. It seems to have been created for an experiment.
Name: Base Reagent

Description: Tree leaves used as weapons by Spions. They are softer than they look.
Name: Spion Tree Leaves

Description: A reagent chemical made by Lucienne to kill the giant vines in Nahash Forest.
Name: Lucienne's Reagent

Description: The teeth of a Spion. They are surprisingly tough.
Name: Spion Teeth

Description: A neutralizing agent given by Vaidotas. It contains a substance able to neutralize Lucienne's Reagent.
Name: Vaidotas' Neutralizer

Description: Herb seeds Lucienne has asked you to plant. It seems they're going to be used to make a reagent.
Name: Experiment Herb Seeds

Description: A sphere given by a villager. It is said to prevent attacks when filled with demon souls.
Name: Soul Sphere

Description: Red blood collected from a demon. It is impossible to find out what its use is.
Name: The red blood of the demons

Description: A sphere purified by the abbot. It exudes divine energy.
Name: Purified Soul Sphere

Description: A scripture containing the doctrines of the Order of the Tree of Truth.
Name: False Scriptures

Description: Random food items left behind at Namoth Cross Parvis. They look like they're about to go bad, but still seem edible.
Name: Edible Food Items

Description: A special reagent created by Lucienne as a result of her research. It was made according to Vaidotas' advice.
Name: Lucienne's Special Reagent

Description: A common stone that can be obtained easily. It is adequately sized to be thrown.
Name: Stone

Description: A horn obtained from a monster. It is very hard.
Name: Coral Horn Piece

Description: A magical stone that can absorb the earth energy.
Name: Earth Magic Stone

Description: A magical stone that can absorb the sea energy.
Name: Sea Magic Stone

Description: A magical stone that can absorb balancing energy.
Name: Balance Magic Stone

Description: A scroll that contains a new binding magic circle. It's safer than the previous magic circles.
Name: Binding Magic Circle Scroll

Description: A magic searching stone that can find the binding magic circle.
Name: Magic Searching Stone

Description: Fragment from a Magic Core that was broken by a demon. The Teleportation Magic Circle won't activate without a Magic Core.
Name: Broken Magic Core Pieces

Description: Essence obtained after defeating a demon. You feel an evil magic.
Name: Evil Demon Essence

Description: Purified essence obtained from demons.
Name: Purified Monster Essence

Description: The Magic Core that formerly provided magic to the teleportation magic circle. It is still unstable and must be looked after with care.
Name: Unstable Magic Core

Description: Sleep Powder that can put Tala Tribespeople to sleep. It is said to be uneffective against others.
Name: Tala Sleep Powder

Description: A necklace taken from the violent Tala Tribe. The gem has been blackened.
Name: Tala Tribe Necklaces

Description: Purified Tala Tribe Necklace. The gem is glowing blue.
Name: Purified Tala Necklace

Description: A magic stone that had been in the possesion of demons. It may fool the restraining device.
Name: Demon Magic Stone

Description: Realized restoration energy. You can feel a warm feeling.
Name: Materialized Recovery

Description: Unstable restoration energy. It will not be easy to realize it without the help of Medena.
Name: Unstable Orb of Restoration

Description: Moss that grew under the influence of the Tevhrin Stalactite Cave's divine energy. It is glowing.
Name: Mysterious Moss

Description: The core that used to be within the Green Zolem. It's an intricately crafted device that moves by magic.
Name: Green Zolem Core

Description: Purified core of a Zolem, which had been moving through evil energy. It has become stronger than the original core.
Name: Purified Zolem Core

Description: A Detection Stone used to find hidden objects. It was given to you by Kupole Medena.
Name: Kupole's Detection Stone

Description: Siute's Pendant. It will shield you from evil magic as it contains protective spells.
Name: Siute's Pendant

Description: Saule's Divine Orb that you received from Serija. It contains the power to control Dalia's seal.
Name: Saule's Divine Orb

Description: Restored form of Saule's Divine Orb. While it does contain power to resist evil energies, the orb has been weakened, only allowing a one-time use.
Name: Restored Saule's Divine Orb

Description: A demon's evil talisman.
Name: Evil Talismans

Description: The first fragment of wand that seems to be broken in pieces.
Name: First Wand Fragment

Description: The second fragment of wand that seems to be broken in pieces.
Name: Second Wand Fragment

Description: A wand restored from broken fragments. Having already been destroyed once, it looks a little unstable.
Name: Unstable Wand

Description: A mysterious pack held by every demon. Using it seems to be the only way to find out what it does. Here goes nothing!
Name: Roana's Holy Water

Description: A plain dagger. The name 'Edward' is engraved in it.
Name: Edward's Dagger

Description: A sturdy-looking bow. The name 'Edward' is engraved in it.
Name: Edward's Bow

Description: An unknown flower growing in the Tamas' habitat.
Name: Unknown Flower

Description: A flask given by Edward for you to collect Cyst fluid.
Name: Edward's Empty Flask

Description: A flask filled with Cyst fluid.
Name: Flask With Cyst Fluid

Description: A herb exuding a delicate fragrance. It smells slightly sweet, too.
Name: Melbania Herb

Description: A flower of intricate tones and a peculiar scent.
Name: Davelae Flower

Description: A large chunk of meat. It looks rather tough.
Name: Cockat Meat

Description: A fragrance Bastille was carrying. It sure smells potent.
Name: Potent Fragrance

Description: A glass flask given by Hunter Bastille for you to collect honey from the Pendrosiums.
Name: Small Glass Flask

Description: A flask filled with Pendrosium honey.
Name: Flask Of Honey

Description: A sphere made to activate blocking devices.
Name: Blocking Sphere

Description: A bizarrely frightening Loftlem eye. It looks disgusting.
Name: Loftlem Eye

Description: The spores of dead liverwort. They look like they could fly away with the slightest breeze.
Name: Dead Liverwort Spores

Description: A vividly-colored stone able to provoke hallucinations in demons.
Name: Hallucination Stone

Description: Pieces of stone taken from the bodies of Moya monsters. The way they sparkle makes them look like gems at a glance.
Name: Sparkling Stones

Description: A crystal fragment from the wand of a Saltisdaughter monster. It possesses a slight glow.
Name: Saltisdaughter Crystal Fragment

Description: An old stone with a faded glow. It looks like someone used it to create a magic circle in the Flooded District a long time ago.
Name: Faded Stone

Description: A bag with emergency food supplies obtained from inside a chest.
Name: Emergency Food Supplies

Description: A heavy bag containing something unknown.
Name: Heavy Bag

Description: An old, faded ring. It features a small inscription on the inside.
Name: Old Ring

Description: A net used for catching fish.
Name: Hand Net

Description: A fish from the lake. It is still alive.
Name: Lake Fish

Description: Documents with information on how to operate the Water Facilities.
Name: Water Facility Management

Description: A written note, penned by someone who was likely in a hurry. It is stained with blood.
Name: Bloody Note

Description: A shining Magic Stone. It looks filled with magic and ready to be used.
Name: Good Magic Stone

Description: A bag for collecting purified water.
Name: Water Bag

Description: Small plants that grow on the lake. They give off a strong divine energy.
Name: Rias Weeds

Description: Powder made from refined Rias Weeds.
Name: Refined Rias Weed Powder

Description: A bag full of purified water.
Name: Water Bag

Description: Tyler's tool for removing traps.
Name: Trap Removal Tool

Description: A bottle filled with poison.
Name: Small Poison Bottle

Description: A stone that can detect magic. It looks expensive.
Name: Magic Detector

Description: Part of an ancient disc. You need the other half in order to read what is written on it.
Name: First Half of Ancient Disc

Description: Part of an ancient disc. You need the other half in order to read what is written on it.
Name: Second Half of Ancient Disc

Description: Orb created to reveal demons who are disguised as humans.
Name: Revealing Orb

Description: A stone imbued with the magic energy of the lake.
Name: Stone with Lake Energy

Description: A stone that absorbs specific types of energy.
Name: Absorbing Stone

Description: Contains instructions on how to craft an arrow using the method developed by the Fletcher Master.
Name: Powerful Arrow Recipe

Description: A material that emits a faint shine, at times found on the continent. Rumors say it can be used to produce powerful tools.
Name: Earth Essence

Description: A type of Obsidian possessing a distinctive red color. It's imbued with the magic energy of the lake.
Name: Natural Obsidian

Description: A type of feather that is exceptionally malleable and robust.
Name: Humming Duke Feather

Description: A highly poisonous plant, avoided even by insects.
Name: Ziburyte

Description: A trap made with Ziburyte poison.
Name: Poisonous Trap

Description: Lean meat obtained from a Humming Duke.
Name: Humming Duke Meat

Description: A water plant that grows on the lake. It possesses outstanding purifying properties.
Name: Pasto

Description: A blue orb imbued with magic. It disappears if taken outside of Baubas Cave.
Name: Magic Orb

Description: There's something written on the stone plate, but it's hard to make out. This item will disappear if you move away from the Stalactite Cave.
Name: Damaged Stone Plate

Description: A blue crystal containing concentrated magic. Its uses are unknown. The crystal disappears if taken outside of Baubas Cave.
Name: Concentrated Blue Crystal

Description: A red crystal containing concentrated magic. Its uses are unknown. The crystal disappears if taken outside of Baubas Cave.
Name: Concentrated Red Crystal

Description: A yellow crystal containing concentrated magic. Its uses are unknown. The crystal disappears if taken outside of Baubas Cave.
Name: Concentrated Yellow Crystal

Description: Beads with cloudy aura. It seems that purification is needed. The item disappears when it leaves Nazarene Tower.
Name: Hazy Sphere

Description: Essence that emits a strong aura of starlight. If you can use the power held inside the starlight essence, you may grow stronger. This item disappears when it leaves Nazarene Tower.
Name: Starlight Essence

Description: A list received from Uska. It's a record on each supporter who promised to help gather donations for the Onmyoji Master's country.
Name: List of Supporters

Description: Saltisdaughter Fur. Can be made into a Fur Piece. 3 pieces of fur can make 1-2 Fur Pieces. Right-click to make.
Name: Saltisdaughter Fur

Description: A fur piece consisting of Saltisdaughter leather and fur.
Name: Saltisdaughter Fur Piece

Description: Not a single bit of water is left on this perfectly dried wood. It looks amazingly sturdy.
Name: Dry Wood

Description: Mushroom Samples. They may or may not be contaminated.
Name: Mushroom Samples

Description: Grape Seed Samples. They may or may not be contaminated.
Name: Grape Seed Samples

Description: Ducky Leather. Can be made into Processed Leather. 2 pieces of Ducky Leather can make 1 Processed Leather. Right-click to make.
Name: Ducky Leather

Description: Processed Ducky Leather that is protected from corruption.
Name: Processed Ducky Leather

Description: A very simple looking brooch. This looks like the brooch Pirate Captain Lowe is looking for.
Name: Simple Brooch

Description: Hard-looking thistle. It gives off an interesting smell.
Name: Hard Thistle

Description: A detector developed to find dimensional stones. Right-click to search for nearby sacks.
Name: Dimensional Stone Detector

Description: A sack containing sample dimensional stones. Something about these stones doesn't feel right.
Name: Sample Dimensional Stone Sack

Description: A spell scroll to prevent food from going bad. Contains a spell that temporarily preserves food. Right click to use the scroll.
Name: Spell Scroll

Description: A divination tool given to you by the Onmyoji Master. The Onmyoji Master has adapted it to fit well with your Focus Training. Use it to change the direction of the moving paper dolls.
Name: Training Shikiban

Description: A note containing the location of the Pied Piper Master.{nl}The Oracle Master's advice was to write down the list of tasks that you will be given once you meet the Pied Piper Master in this note.
Name: Oracle Master's Note

Description: An ingredient required in the making of the Plague Doctor Master's cure.{nl}It has a distinct fragrance.
Name: Perilla

Description: The Plague Doctor Master's cure for mental illness.{nl}The effectiveness of the cure has not yet been tested and its potency is known to reduce over time.
Name: Cure for Mental Illness

Description: Empty glass bottle. Collect the Glowing Blue Sand by using this item in places around Igti Coast.
Name: Empty Glass Bottle

Description: A glass bottle full of Glowing Blue Sand.
Name: Full Glass Bottle

Description: A cure for mental illness bottled in a special vessel made by the Chronomancer Master. There is a subdued glow radiating from the vessel.
Name: Mental Illness Cure

Description: The cure for mental illness blessed by the Priest Master. It is quietly glowing.
Name: Blessed Cure for Mental Illness

Description: A flute for training given by the Pied Piper Master.{nl}Use the flute in Branginti Hill on Altar Way.{nl}Cooldown time 3 seconds.
Name: Old Flute

Description: A potion obtained from the Assassin Master.{nl}Use it under the Pasagos Cliff in Ramstis Ridge.{nl}Cooldown of 3 seconds.
Name: Hasisas Base Potion

Description: A flower with a slight yellow shade.
Name: Yellow Flower

Description: A red-tinted flower.
Name: Red Flower

Description: A snow-white flower.
Name: White Flower

Description: Butterfly-shaped yellow leaf.{nl}Looks like it might fly away immediately.
Name: Yellow Butterfly Leaf

Description: Butterfly-shaped red leaf.{nl}Looks like it might fly away immediately.
Name: Red Butterfly Leaf

Description: Butterfly-shaped white leaf.{nl}Looks like it might fly away immediately.
Name: White Butterfly Leaf

Description: Mysterious transparent crystal.{nl}It is radiating with holy energy.
Name: Transparent Crystal

Description: A scroll for sealing away magic.
Name: Sealing Scroll

Description: A scroll that allows for the caster to bind someone.
Name: Binding Scroll

Description: A mysterious, yet beautiful, seed.{nl}A strange power can be felt when holding it.
Name: Mysterious Seed

Description: A scroll for sealing away magic.
Name: Sealing Scroll

Description: The only seed of the Divine Tree, given by the Goddess Medeina.{nl}It has astonishing properties.
Name: Seed of the Divine Tree

Description: Lively and vivacious grass.
Name: Vivacious Grass

Description: A holy branch full of divine energy.
Name: Holy Branch

Description: An unbinding scroll held by a Red Banterer.
Name: Unbinding Scroll

Description: An orb given to Kupole Ilona by the Goddess Medeina{nl}Ilona believes that she can use this orb to locate Medeina.
Name: Orb filled with Natural Energy

Description: An essence found where a Red Banterer used to stand.{nl}It feels evil.
Name: Red Banterer Essence

Description: A scroll for sealing away magic.
Name: Sealing Scroll

Description: The only seed of the Divine Tree, given by the Goddess Medeina.{nl}Most of its powers had been sealed away through the altar.
Name: Sealed Seed of the Divine Tree

Description: The only seed of the Divine Tree, given by the Goddess Medeina.{nl}Most of its powers had been sealed away through the altar.
Name: Sealed Seed of the Divine Tree

Description: A disc found in the Wandering Sanctuary.{nl}It's said to sometimes glow a red light.
Name: Old Disc

Description: An unidentified fragment.{nl}It glows an ominous red light.
Name: Red Fragment

Description: Requested by Samsonas as tribute to offer to the goddesses. Could this be considered a proper tribute?
Name: Rajatadpole Meat

Description: A diary partially burnt by fire. A lot of it is damaged, which makes it difficult to read.
Name: Burnt Diary

Description: A note containing the only legible parts of the burnt diary.
Name: Note With Content From Burnt Diary

Description: A painting partially burnt by fire. It portrays a bizarrely-shaped object similar to a gem and an unknown monster.
Name: Burnt Painting

Description: A special herb that exudes a very particular smell. It is said to be used in erasing traces of people's scent.
Name: Blue Herb

Description: A material used as bait to attract Hydras.{nl}Could Hydras really like this meat?
Name: Bait Meat

Description: A plant that grows a yellow flower. It can be chewed in case of emergency as it offers strong painkilling effects.
Name: Markazi Flower

Description: Grease made from monster lard. Highly flammable.
Name: Gooey Grease

Description: A highly flammable lard. It becomes even more flammable after being refined.
Name: Rajapearlite Lard

Description: Completed bait. Tyronas Hydra really likes this.
Name: Modis' Special Bait

Description: Tribute to be offered to a suspicious obelisk.{nl}It contains monster meat.
Name: Sack with Offerings

Description: A sparkly blue fragment discovered in Sicarius. It looks like it could be used to activate a device.
Name: Sparkly Blue Fragment

Description: A sparkly red fragment discovered in Sicarius. It looks like it could be used to activate a device.
Name: Sparkly Red Fragment

Description: A key made of sparkling blue fragments. Used to activate a certain device.
Name: Sicarius Key

Description: A suspicious pouch found buried in the ground. It exudes a strange smell.
Name: Suspicious Pouch

Description: A peculiar-looking piece of coral. It seems to have come from a never-before-seen species.
Name: Peculiar Coral Fragment

Description: A piece of Greentoshell shell. It can be ground and used as an ointment ingredient.
Name: Greentoshell Shell Fragment

Description: Moss that grows on the bodies of Lapasape Mages. It can be used as an ingredient for ointment.
Name: Blue Lapasape Moss

Description: A compass borrowed from a merchant, useful in finding a tool able to open a magically-locked chest. It points to nearby magic objects.
Name: Merchant's Magic Detector

Description: An old backpack that reacts to the magic detector. It contains several objects of unknown use...
Name: Old Backpack

Description: A peculiar-looking piece of coral. It is said to have come from a never-before-seen species. Investigate nearby corals.
Name: Arnim Coral Piece

Description: Pollen from a Yellow Griba. It exudes a strange smell, said to clear the mind of those who inhale it.
Name: Yellow Griba Pollen

Description: Said to relieve pain and help cure ailments. Used as a painkiller by the Dievdirbys in Grynas Forest.
Name: Yellow Sapous

Description: A stone said to carry the power of a mysterious spirit. The Raucous Owl Sculpture wants to use it to make an amulet.
Name: Spirit Stone

Description: A suspicious pouch filled with powder, used by Stoulets in rituals. The Raucous Owl Sculpture wants to use it to make an amulet.
Name: Ritual Pouch

Description: A crystal made by the Raucous Owl Sculpture. Place it near the Sleeping Owl Sculpture to protect it from monsters.
Name: Protective Crystal

Description: A fluid obtained from Green Sockets. It is very sticky and looks like it can be used as glue.
Name: Sticky Liquid

Description: Remains of a Brown Stoulet Archer's broken bow. Very crudely built, but can still be used in emergencies.
Name: Broken Bow

Description: A dried up, shrivelled black stem. Its use for carving is uncertain.
Name: Shrivelled Black Stem

Description: Stems of a Black Old Kepa. They're shrivelled up but look like they can be used for carving.
Name: Black Old Kepa Stems

Description: Hook taken from the hands of a Red Puragi. It looks completely broken, but can still be used for carving.
Name: Red Puragi Hook

Description: The leaves of a Blue Ridimed. They look like they can be used for carving.
Name: Blue Ridimed Leaves

Description: Fruit found inside a pile of greenery. It smells sweet. Ridimeds are said to love this fruit.
Name: Peculiarly Scented Fruit

Description: An old carving knife. There's a name written on it but it's barely visible anymore. It could belong to a Dievdirbys.
Name: Old Carving Knife

Description: A rudimentary dagger. It's sharper than it looks and continuously exudes evil energy.
Name: Evil Energy Dagger

Description: A broken amulet. It features a dark gem on the front. A faint evil energy can be felt coming from it.
Name: Broken Amulet

Description: A sculpture by Sculptor Tesla. It seems to exude divine energy. Said to help weaken and clean away the evil energy around it.
Name: Suppressing Sculpture

Description: An orb with a faint greenish glow. It is charged with vital energy whenever monsters are defeated by whoever carries it.
Name: Faintly Glowing Orb

Description: A sculpture by Dievdirbys Asel. Inherited from Tesla, it is said to have the power to purify evil energy and any objects contaminated by it.
Name: Purifying Sculpture

Description: The Quiet Owl Sculpture believes these leaves can appease the spirits.
Name: Blue Sakmoli Leaves

Description: A small owl sculpture made by Dievdirbys Asel. The Owl Sculptures believe that, if imbued with power, it can help access the memories of the Broken Owl Sculpture.
Name: Carve Owl

Description: Part of a blue coral. After it's processed, it's going to be used to make an offering for Goddess Jurate.
Name: Blue Coral

Description: A pouch filled with an odd-smelling powder. Bertha says that, if buried under the ground, the powder has the power to attract monsters.
Name: Odd-Smelling Pouch

Description: An intact piece of a Gapcrab shell. Free of cracks or chips, it can be used to create jewelry.
Name: Intact Gap Crab Shell Fragment

Description: A coral handcrafted by Accessory Merchant Joana. One may as well call it an actual jewel.
Name: Crafted Coral

Description: Said to reflect the energy of the sea in its cerulean color.
Name: Cerulean Stone

Description: A pendant given by Daroul. Daroul says the energy of defeated monsters will be absorbed into this amulet.
Name: Daroul's Pendant

Description: A dagger used by the suspicious person following the little girl. It's sharper than it looks and has strange carvings on it.
Name: Purified Dagger

Description: Holy water given by Bertha, said to hold the energy of the sea. When poured over a rock, its color turns into a shade of green.
Name: Ocean's Divine Water

Description: Pag Clamper's Core. It is required to fill Jaonus Altar with divine energy. Does it really have anything to do with divine energy?
Name: Pag Clamper's Core

Description: Keepsakes taken from the coffin. It is said to contain the resentment of the dead. Does it really have anything to do with filling the altar with divine energy? This is becoming even more suspicious.
Name: Keepsakes Containing the Resentment of the Dead

Description: A doctrine that has been scribbled on a piece of paper. It looks extremely shoddy. "Death is our only true God."
Name: Temporary Doctrine Chapter 1

Description: A doctrine that has been scribbled on a piece of paper. It looks extremely shoddy. "We become complete by bathing in the blood of humans."
Name: Temporary Doctrine Chapter 2

Description: A doctrine that has been scribbled on a piece of paper. It looks extremely shoddy. "Creed - Sacrifice humans and complete death."
Name: Temporary Doctrine Chapter 3

Description: A Pag Doper's oil bottle. It has a strange scent. Can you light fires with this oil?
Name: Pag Doper's Oil Bottle

Description: A doctrine that has been scribbled on a piece of paper. It looks extremely shoddy and is also damaged, making it difficult to read. "Death is the greatest blessing of all."
Name: Damaged Temporary Doctrine

Description: The book of judgement given to you by Judge Rymis. It is said to give its owner immense divine power if there is anyone who refuses to convert or accept judgement.
Name: Book of Judgment

Description: A strange smelling fluid from Nuttafly and Nuttabug. According to Kupole Lina, it is used as a base ingredient in supplements.
Name: Nutta Fluid

Description: Leaves that have fallen near trees. Kupole Lina says that supplements are created with these, and monster fluids.
Name: Fallen Leaves

Description: A strange smelling bottle that holds Kupole Lina's supplement. You have been asked to fill empty bottles with it.
Name: Lina's Supplement Bottle

Description: Medicine you've been given to be use while collecting monster essence. Weakened monsters will be paralyzed by it.
Name: Tranquilizer

Description: Rodejokel essence that was requested by Kupole Lina. You will have to paralyze weakened Rodejokels in order to obtain it.
Name: Rodejokel Essence

Description: Glimmering powder gathered from Nuttafly. It is used to activate Magic Spheres.
Name: Glimmering Powder

Description: Blue moss that is said to grow in Nheto Forest. Said to be found under boulders in fall.
Name: Blue Nheto Moss

Description: A dark yellow herb. Cesaris has asked you to gather yellow herbs that stand out in between the red leaves.
Name: Lyciu Herbs

Description: A whistle that can call Iyran to your location. Blow the whistle if Iyran is too far away.
Name: Cesaris' Whistle

Description: Vhelis roots found by Iyran. You can't see the difference.
Name: Vhelis Roots

Description: A mysterious brown powder. It is sprinkled over the logs that Lumberjack Dowedas had asked you to bring.
Name: Brown Powder

Description: A blood sample that Chronomancer Ida asked you to bring. It has not had the time to solidify yet.
Name: Blood Sample

Description: A blood sample taken at the request of Chronomancer Ida. It solidified as soon as you left Nheto Forest.
Name: Solidified Blood Sample

Description: A report written by Forest Ranger Bronius at the request of Chronomancer Ida. It contains information about leaves and Blue Nheto Moss.
Name: Forest Ranger's Report

Description: A report written by Herbalist Cesaris at the request of Chronomancer Ida. It contains information about 6 types of herbs.
Name: Herbalist's Report

Description: A report written by Lumberjack Dowedas at the request of Chronomancer Ida. It contains information about the weather, climate and aging circles.
Name: Lumberjack's Report

Description: A report you have received from the Chronomancer about the forest. Right-click to read.
Name: Report on the Relation Between the Forest and Medzio Diena

Description: A fragment from a shoddy rag doll. Perhaps this is the doll mentioned in Morkus' dairy.
Name: Rag Doll Fragment

Description: Thick stems that had been buried underground. Can be used to craft a leaf whistle.
Name: Sturdy Roots

Description: Willitte's shovel. A sturdy shovel despite being extremely worn. It seems to be more than capable of digging up bulky roots.
Name: Willitte's Shovel

Description: Potion used to remove dye. Morkus wishes to spray this on a green tree.
Name: Organic Solvent

Description: A necklace that Morkus found on the ground. You seem to remember seeing it being used somewhere...
Name: Hidden Necklace

Description: A report written by Chronomancer Ida to be given to the Chronomancer Master. It contains information about the situation in Nheto Forest.
Name: Ida's Report

Description: An old carving knife. There's a name written on it but it's barely visible anymore. It could belong to a Dievdirbys.
Name: Old Carving Knife

Description: Orders written in unreadable demon letters. Kupoles may be able to make sense of it.
Name: Demon Orders

Description: Orders written in unreadable demon letters. Kupoles may be able to make sense of it.
Name: Small Stone Fragment

Description: The Kupole has asked you to gather the demon's strength. Defeat demons in the surrounding area with this orb in order to collect their energy.
Name: Essence Collection Orb

Description: An Orb of Divine Detection crafted by the Kupole. It will react to any divine energy in the area.
Name: Orb of Divine Detection

Description: Essence collected from demons. Used to craft an alarm that will detect any incoming demons.
Name: Sealed Demon's Power

Description: Essence collected from demons. Used to craft an alarm that will detect any incoming demons.
Name: Kupole's Alarm Crystal

Description: A fragment suspected of being a trace of Ausrine. It appears to have marks of something being engraved on it.
Name: Ausrine's First Trace

Description: A fragment suspected of being a trace of Ausrine. It seems to be a damaged mirror. Perhaps it was used in some sort of ritual.
Name: Ausrine's Second Trace

Description: A fragment suspected of being a trace of Ausrine. It seems to be a piece of glass from something bigger. It reacts to divine energy.
Name: Ausrine's Third Trace

Description: Orders written in unreadable demon letters. It seems to be different from the one you previously found. The Kupoles may be able to make sense of it.
Name: Lieutenant's Demon Orders

Description: A stone fragment you found in the ruins. Looks like it's a fragment from the destroyed altar.
Name: An Unknown Object

Description: An object that appears to be a trace of Ausrine. It is a wooden statue that is severely damaged.
Name: Ausrine's Fourth Trace

Description: An object that appears to be a trace of Ausrine. It is a severely damaged necklace that may have been used as part of a ritual.
Name: Ausrine's Fifth Trace

Description: A Magic Stone fragment that contains a demon's power. Kupole Leda seems to plan on crafting a divine energy Detection Orb by using debris from the Interferance Magic Circle and the fragment.
Name: Demon Magic Stone Fragment

Description: Kupole Leda seems to plan on crafting a divine energy Detection Orb by using debris from the Interferance Magic Circle and the fragment.
Name: Interferance Magic Circle Debris

Description: Gosal Horn. The Falconer Master has told you to obtain this horn by defeating the Gosal in Khonot Forest to prove your skills.
Name: Gosal Horn

Description: A crystal given to you by the Hackapell Master. It is said to use the Sanctuary's energy to cure illness. You have been tasked with charging it with energy as the Hackapell Master is too busy to do so on behalf of the Pardoner Master.
Name: Crystal of Restoration

Description: An old coin found recently on the coast. Said to be extremely valuable.
Name: Old Commemorative Coin

Description: A red crystal that has been passed down the Hummil Family. It reacts to any blue crystals near it.
Name: The Hummil Family's Red Crystal

Description: A blue crystal that has been passed down the Hummil Family. It reacts to any red crystals near it.
Name: The Hummil Family's Blue Crystal

Description: Documents containing unrecognizable letters. It is in bad shape, as it was abandoned in the grass. Difficult to read, but has a seal in the shape of a tree.
Name: Suspicious Documents

Description: Sage Master'Encyclopedia of Masters, Chapter 2'A letter sent to the Fencer Master for the book. It details the contents about the Fencer Master and an inquiry to confirm.
Name: Sage Master's Letter

Description: Sage Master'Encyclopedia of Masters, Chapter 2'A letter sent to the Necromancer Master for the book. It details the contents about the Necromancer Master and an inquiry to confirm.
Name: Sage Master's Letter

Description: A reply to the Sage Master written by the Druid Master. It features the Druid Master's life story from the childhood to the masterhood.
Name: Druid Master's Reply

Description: A reply written by the Fencer Master. It features the connection between the Fencer Masterhood and her family and why the role came to her after Medzio Diena.
Name: Fencer Master's Reply

Description: A reply written by the Necromancer Master. It features the story behind her way to the masterhood and her achievements.
Name: Necromancer Master's Reply

Description: A book heavily weathered and damaged. Only the letters on its cover are  barely legible. Take this to the Fencer Master.
Name: Hutton's Swordsmanship Textbook

Description: The crystal given to you by the Linker Master for the investigation. The Master requested you to defeat Gazing Golem.
Name: Linker Master's Magic Crystal

Description: A small fragment fallen out of Gazing Golem. What was the Linker Master investigating?
Name: Gazing Golem Fragment

Description: The Magic Core of Gazing Golem, it gives an impression of gazing into my soul.
Name: Gazing Golem Magic Core

Description: A device made by the Linker Master to track the demons linked to Gazing Golem. It is said that when it is installed, the identity of the one who has sent Gazing Golem. Set this up on the spot told by the Linker Master without getting detected by Gazing Golem.
Name: Link Tracking Device

Description: A magic stone devised by the Linker Master. It disrupts Gazing Golem's perception and render you invisible to it. Caution: Getting too close to the target will get you detected.
Name: Camouflage Crystal

Description: A certificate written by Druid Master Gina Greene. It says that'Herbalist Calsis'I am told that his family can get money from the Kedora Merchant Alliance or from Pardoner Master or the amount of money Greene has written down.
Name: Gina Greene's Certificate

Description: Herbalist Calsis' diary. In it, he wrote about his trip to Dadan Jungle and about his daughter.
Name: Calsis' Diary

Description: These flowers go by the name of Arzeli. They are very expensive and are said to relieve the symptoms of any disease.
Name: Arzeli

Description: The powder given by Baron Muchausen. He claimed it has the exorcising effect. Does it though?
Name: Holy Powder

Description: A bag containing a crystal made and given by Baron Muchausen. He did say it drives out monsters. Does it? I mean, really, I have my doubts.
Name: Suspicious Crystal Pouch

Description: The dried leaves requested by Baron Muchausen. The leaves in the forest are always dried up nowadays.
Name: Nheto Forest Leaves

Description: The reagent made by Baron Muchausen. Mixed with dried leaves and Goddess knows what. Will it work?
Name: Munchausen's Reagent

Description: The crystal the Baron Munchause gave you. He said it drives ghosts away. Like always, it is a rather odd and peculiar object.
Name: Anti-ghost Crystal

Description: Contains the materials that  were stolen from Revelator Pudhin. It seems to contain some food and potions.
Name: Stolen Supplies

Description: The coral powder that Nimrah Damsel had. I do not know where it is used, but according to the translator Mirius, it is said to be helpful for healing.
Name: Coral powder of Nimrah Damsel

Description: A blue coral reef obtained from Zeteor Coast. It is said to be used in ceremonies for calling Goddess Jurate.
Name: Zeteor Coast's Blue Coral Reef

Description: A red fragment found on the Tolata Sandbank. It emits a wicked energy and is quite discomforting.
Name: Nasty Red Fragment

Description: It is said to be a mirror used in ceremonies and rituals as the sacred material of the Goddess Jurate, sealed by the Demons. Its reflection is clouded by an evil aura.
Name: Sealed Holy Artifact of Jurate

Description: The sacred treasure of Jurate that tradition person Ugnius had. It was said that it was a necklace worn by a priest who conducted rituals and ordinances.
Name: Jurate's First Holy Artifact

Description: Jurate's second artifact, although the Demons sealed it, it is a mirror that was used in rituals and as a sanctuary that washed away demonic energy using the aura of the sea.
Name: Jurate's Second Holy Artifact

Description: Luxuriously decorated water. They are said to be water bottles containing water for purification Ritual. The traitor, Ugnius, went to Letave Plateau and asked him to fill up the water of the sea.
Name: Loremaster Bottle

Description: Blue moss. It is said to be used for ritual burning after being dried.
Name: Jurate's Moss

Description: A hand-crafted talisman enchanted with the blessings of Goddess Jurate. It's made from the blue coral reefs that grow on Iotheo Coast. According to Revelator Nichi, it is said to be able to banish evil auras.
Name: Blessed Coral Talisman

Description: Right-click to use. Check the Character Settings tab for the registered color.
Name: Pink Hair Dye

Description: An unknown fragment. It's hard to tell what it can be used for, but it emits a faint magic.
Name: Magic Stone Fragment

Description: Increases +3 movement speed for 300 seconds. Effects apply only inside the Rancid Labyrinth, Balaam Camp Site and Michmas Temple. Right-click to use. Cooldown of 60 seconds.
Name: Magic Stone of Speed

Description: Increases +140 physical critical attack for 300 seconds. Effects apply only inside the Rancid Labyrinth, Balaam Camp Site and Michmas Temple. Right-click to use. Cooldown of 60 seconds.
Name: Magic Stone of Wrath

Description: Increases +130 magic critical attack for 300 seconds. Effects apply only inside the Rancid Labyrinth, Balaam Camp Site and Michmas Temple. Right-click to use. Cooldown of 60 seconds.
Name: Magic Stone of Illusion

Description: A red fragment from a demon device. It releases evil energy and magic.
Name: Demon Device Fragment

Description: A finely decorated water bottle. Loremaster Emmanuelis filled it with holy water intended for purification.
Name: Loremaster Bottle

Description: A necklace that feels both sacred and strangely eerie. According to the Zealot Master, it is a tool used to teach newcomers.
Name: Zealot Crystal Necklace

Description: A tasty pumpkin-shaped treat obtained from the Halloween event dungeon. You can obtain a maximum of 300 treats per run.
Name: Sugar Treat

Description: The Zealot Order: Fervor and Devotion. A book describing the Zealot an order written by Inquisitor Thomas Iquinostasys
Name: The Zealot Order: Fervor and Devotion

Description: A book describing the Zealots: A History. The book written by Zealot Peter Marshall.
Name: Zealots: A History

Description: A book describing the Zealot and Goddess of Divine Energy written by Thomas Iquinostasys
Name: Zealots and Divine Power
